s because this makes discovery of the usage pattern much more difficult, both for designers and for users of raw markup.","pos":[15648,15964],"source":" (For more information, see [x:FactoryMethod Directive](../../../docs/framework/xaml-services/x-factorymethod-directive.md).) However, you should not use these patterns for markup extension purposes because this makes discovery of the usage pattern much more difficult, both for designers and for users of raw markup."},{"pos":[16033,16074],"content":"Attributing for a Custom Markup Extension","linkify":"Attributing for a Custom Markup Extension","nodes":[{"content":"Attributing for a Custom Markup Extension","pos":[0,41]}]},{"content":"To support both design environments and certain XAML object writer scenarios, you should attribute a markup extension support type with several CLR attributes.","pos":[16078,16237]},{"content":"These attributes report the intended markup extension usage.","pos":[16238,16298]},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Markup.MarkupExtensionReturnTypeAttribute&gt;</ph> reports the <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Type&gt;</ph> information for the object type that <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Markup.ArrayExtension.ProvideValue%2A&gt;</ph> returns.","pos":[16305,16505],"source":"<xref:System.Windows.Markup.MarkupExtensionReturnTypeAttribute> reports the <xref:System.Type> information for the object type that <xref:System.Windows.Markup.ArrayExtension.ProvideValue%2A> returns."},{"content":"By its pure signature, <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Markup.ArrayExtension.ProvideValue%2A&gt;</ph> returns <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Object&gt;</ph>.","pos":[16506,16618],"source":" By its pure signature, <xref:System.Windows.Markup.ArrayExtension.ProvideValue%2A> returns <xref:System.Object>."},{"content":"But various consumers might want more precise return type information.","pos":[16619,16689]},{"content":"This includes:","pos":[16690,16704]},{"content":"Designers and I